comment: Work is easy, exams seem hard but are manageable with a bit of studying. Lectures are a bit boring. He is a nice guy though, and knows what he is talking about.

I have no idea why Paul has a 3.3 rating. He is the man, he knows what hes talking about, and the class is cake. The workload is super light, and while the exams arent I didnt even have to watch a lecture to pass, they are very doable if you somewhat pay attention. Definitely recommend this class.

One of the best teachers I've had in college thus far. Super respectful, articulate, interesting teaching method. Not a heavy workload, exams don't ask too much of you, easy and infrequent discussion posts required. Clearly very passionate/knowledgable about supply chain which makes the course more enjoyable.

He lets you use a cheat sheet on exams so anyone saying the exams are hard needs to step up their game. All questions are based on practice problems in class. Show up, pay attention, and you'll be fine. His lectures are pretty entertaining, and you gotta love his self-deprecating humor.

I can tell that Paul really cares about Supply Chain Mgt., but for somebody who has no desire in it and is just taking it because its required, I really struggled in this class. There is barely any homework which is nice, but the tests were brutal and had nothing to do with the study guides or lectures. If this is not your passion, steer clear.

Vanderspek is a nice guy. However, his exams are pretty difficult, and some topics that you study for are not on the exam. This is the hardest class I have taken at CSU, and after this, I don't think I would pursue Supply Chain. Cheat sheets are helpful which I appreciate, but the lectures are pretty boring.

The exams are not easy. You get to have a cheat sheet, but it does not really help because a lot of the stuff that is on the study guide and on the slide is not on the exam. I would put the whole study guide onto my cheat sheet and it did not help.

Paul is one of the most relaxed professors I've ever taken a class from. His quizzes are super easy, the exams are relatively easy, and you have one multi-part group project throughout the semester. I learned a lot about operations from Paul.
ratingTags: BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES--GROUP PROJECTS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Not personable. I got the impression that he didn't care for student understanding, but spent most of his time handling the business he runs. Didn't respond to any of my emails all semester. Nice guy, but the tests were way more difficult than the concepts that seemed to "make sense" in class. PowerPoints weren't helpful, unfair +/- grading used.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Get ready to read--TEST HEAVY

comment: Not much assigned homework which can be both good or bad depending on how you learn. The exams are difficult but you do get a cheat sheet which you better hope has what you need. read the chapters before class and make sure you review the homework well and you'll be fine.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Awesome teacher, tests are a bit difficult but you are able to use a cheat sheet!

I really enjoyed having Nyssa. Her class was organized, straightforward, and I felt like my Spanish improved. However, she was a very slow grader and didnt enter any of the big assignments until the end of the semester. Also, the tests were very different from the HW and difficult, so make sure to study. I would definitely take her again though!

Nyssa is extremely caring about her students, but appeared to be too busy to properly teach the course. It seemed to be a teach yourself kind of course- only met 1x a week. Short prerecorded videos and readings, then really hard quizzes without any real practice of the grammar learned. Timed essays which were reasonable and applied the material.

I thought Dr. McFarland did a good job of translating CHEM111 into an online class. The class was organized and expectations clear. However, I felt that she wasnt very approachable. I went to her office hours and she was a little intimidating and difficult to ask questions to. CHEM111 can be tricky, but if you put in some effort, you will be fine.

You can tell MacFarland is caring towards her students. You did not need to attend the zoom meetings as all her lectures were recorded which was nice to review before tests. Pretty average for gen chem, but definitely would recommend over the other chemistry professors. Homework is time consuming, but it is the same for all chem 111 classes.

This class might have been good not online. But Professor MAcFarland has no idea how to teach an online class and it shows. She races through everything, barely explains some concepts, then tests you hard on those concepts. It's quite annoying knowing that when taught right, chem can be a really fun class. This class, however, is not fun.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Test heavy

comment: Kerry is an incredibly kind and effective teacher. It's very clear that she cares so much about her students and teaching. It's also clear that she's spent a long time refining how and what she teaches in chemistry because she is so clear and systematic with how she introduces material. Overall, excellent instructor and great person.

By far the hardest I've ever taken. Attendance isn't "mandatory" , but there are daily clicker questions that influence your grade so definitely show up. The course grade relies heavily on tests, which, if you're like me and get test anxiety, can be tough, but overall I left the class feeling like I had a solid understanding of the material.

The content is dry but Kerry explains it very clearly and always takes questions. If you come to class and do the homework, you'll learn what you need to know for the tests. Take advantage of the practice exams on Canvas to be best prepared for tests.

There is a lot of homework in the class, but if yo I do that and attend lecture/recitation, the class is easy. She is easily one of the best professors I have had, doing demonstrations during class and was very understanding with extenuating circumstances. The whole class gave her a standing ovation at the end of the semester.

Kerry is a great professor for CHEM111. She is kind and caring and is willing to work with you. She is very nice and teaches the hard topic of chemistry in an easy to understand way. Any negative review is a reflection of the Chem department as a whole and not her. Make sure to stay on top of your work!
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Lecture heavy

comment: Good prof.... terribly hard class. Testing makes up 60% of your grade and you can complete all the homework assignments, go to lecture, and attend recitation and still fail the class if you struggle with the material and test poorly. I suggest pairing this course with easily-ish classes in order to succeed.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Lots of homework--Test heavy

comment: She is a very good lecturer, however she is at all flexible when it comes to personal issues impacting coursework during the semester.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Accessible outside class--Amazing lectures

comment: She is a great professor and really wants you to succeed and do well. She takes notes with you in class on paper so you know what topics to understand and material to study for exams. She explains things really well but sometimes she moves too fast. Listening to her lectures over and reviewing her notes was helpful. Just do the homework on time!
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Test heavy

comment: She makes Chemistry easy to understand and uses fun examples like bringing legos. She is super nice and easy to approach. This is a hard class however and has lots of homework.

comment: tons of homework. moves really fast in lectures. shes good at explaining and very nice. Chem department for general chemistry is not super great.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Lecture heavy

comment: This class is less based on your professor and more based on the department. I had a fairly difficult time. LOTS of homework, but that's just the course. Dr. MacFarland is a bit awkward, which is I think why people consider her boring. That being said, she wants you to learn and knows the subject well. Solid choice for this course in my opinion.

She was a good teacher but her teaching style did not fit for me. Lectures were super boring and could have been explained better. The department is kinda slacking but she is one of the better chem teachers. By far hardest class i have ever taken. DO NOT SKIP OR YOU WILL NOT PASS
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: Chemistry is hard but I think Prof Macfarland was the best professor I could have had. She is not by any means going to "entertain" you but she will teach you everything you need to know in a very effective way. She helps as much as she can and wants to see you succeed. Don't be afraid to ask for help because she'll always be willing.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Amazing lectures

comment: Always makes class interesting and she genuinely cares about her students' success.

Really good with staying on topic during lectures and giving clear and easy to understand lectures. Attendance isn't mandatory but there was at least 2 clicker questions each lecture for points (so semi mandatory if you want those points). Overall really good teacher, would gladly take another class taught by her!

This class was worthless. The focus on actual chemistry is minimal. There are two tests that cover chemistry and I received an F on both and still passed the class with an A+. As for Dr. M, I was frustrated when the class ended and I still hadn't received a grade for my FIRST assignment until two months later. She literally didn't teach us anything
Really explains things well. Go to office hours, pay attention, do the homework and you'll pass.

Her test are so extremely hard. Usually the average for most tests was between a 55% to 75% so make sure to study a lot. Tons of homework, at least five times a week. Sometimes her lectures could be boring but it was chemistry so I don't blame her for that.

She was a good teacher and clearly was passionate about chemistry. Went over lots of examples in class and it was helpful to go to lectures. There is a lot of homework in the class so be prepared to work.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: She is very thorough and always gives well prepared lectures. All homework assignments are the same for all sections of 111 which is a somewhat heavy workload. Rewatching her lectures is by far the best way to prepare for the exams. You will do well if you complete all of the HW on time since it is 45% of the final grade.

Dr. MacFarland is a fantastic teacher.  She's a little soft-spoken which is a small challenge when the class gets loud.  She's easily accessible in office hours and cares about her students.  Her tongue-in-cheek/snarky comments in lecture kept me engaged during lecture.  A solid choice for anyone trying to make gen chem less painful.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--Hilarious

comment: I don't know what the other rating are talking about but she is not that great. Her voice is obnoxious and it's an extremely boring class. High school chemistry pretty much. Very hard not to fall asleep during lectures. There's an exam every 3 weeks which is annoying. The chem department here is a trainwreck and needs some serious restructuring.

She writes down everything she says making it super easy to take notes. There is a textbook required for this class but her lectures are so good that you won't have to look at the textbook to pass. She makes the concepts so simple it is hard not to pass with a good grade. After leaving lecture everyday, everything seems like common sense.
This professor will save your General Chemistry experience. She is very nice, clear and wants to help you succeed.
mega babe and good at her job

This professor was by far the best teacher I could have gotten for Chem111. This course is tough & challenging, but she goes through every topic thoroughly making it hard for you NOT to understand the material. She writes out everything she says, making it super easy to take notes & follow along. Sign up for the section she teaches!
If you must tough out the chemistry courses here, she is the professor to take them with. Her lectures are excellent and she does lots of examples.

Her lectures were always really easy to follow and even the difficult concepts were easy to understand. She teaches in a way that makes the hard stuff seem easy! So long as you come to class and pay attention, you'll do fine!

Kerry is incredible! She's so passionate about the subject. Very kind, sweet woman. Always willing to help you out extra if you need it. She's good about keeping up on the gradebook. Having her definitely made the class more bearable.
Fantastic teacher. Would have stuggled without her

Professor MacFarland is a great professor. She explained well and made chemistry a lot easier to learn for me than in the past. She's definitely knowledgeable and is more than willing to help you out if you seek that extra help outside of class. Attending class everyday was very helpful.

For the reputation the chemistry department has here at CSU, MacFarland wasn't a bad teacher at all, though the class was pretty difficult. Take notes from the book and go to class each day and its definitely manageable.

Ana is a tough profesor, but I learned a lot of Spanish and her class was well worth it. She is very caring and willing to help. She is approachable when it comes to getting feedback and she even gave me extended time on a test because I felt rushed on the last one. There are lots of assignments, so many opportunities to raise your grade.

Don't take if it's online. She doesn't have any meetings which makes taking a Spanish class pointless. I've asked her several times to meet virtual because I was confused and she would say no it's actually really easy and tries to explain it over the email. This lead me to doing awful on quizzes and tests and she would still refuse to help.

I honestly wouldn't recommend this class unless you are very advanced. I am a native Spanish speaker the professor grades things very hard and despite there always being different answers to something, it ALWAYS has to be done her way. If you are more advanced in the language itself she expects more from you so she isn't fair with the grading
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Group projects--Tough grader

comment: I really liked her for LSPA300! If you participate in class, pay attention, and study for her exams, you will do great. I know several people that didn't liked her because she can be a hard grader, but overall she's great. I also liked her because she's super organized and clearly follows the syllabus

Professor Fairchild was by far the funniest teacher I've ever had! She was very engaging in her lectures. The amount of homework was very manageable and it was always helpful (never busy work). ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Hilarious--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: Ana Fairchild speaks very clearly with gestures to make sure you understand everything she says. Ana is an enthusiastic teacher. She makes learning fun and incorporates group activities. She's a hard grader, but it's because she wants you to improve. She's funny and will help you out whenever you are stuck or just need clarification.
I took Ana for LSPA 400 and 345 she is an amazing professor, I believe that most students that don't like Ana are because she actually wants you to learn the language and be fluent.

Ana is one of the nicest professors I have ever met! I took LSPA 345 and 400 with her and if you go to class and participate, you will do fine. Highly recommend!

comment: Fairchild is by far the worst LSPA teacher I have ever had (& Im a minor in in it) & treats her students like babies. She views linguistics as a black and white subject- you must read her mind to get an A. Worst part is she doesnt provide enough specific practice for her requirements. I can be acing online practice tests and get a C on hers. AVOID!

I thought that Ana was unreasonable in her grading and expectations for you to not only read her mind but be okay with being treated like children or high school students rather than adults in a 300 level college course.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Ana is hilarious and makes Spanish grammar so much easier and entertaining. She makes the textbook so it's only $12 and is extremely cut and dry. She grades hard, but I've never learned so much, so easily from a Spanish professor before. Loved her!

She is the best professor I have had for any LSPA class. She likes to spend class in a discussion form and also doing grammar examples on the board. I really enjoyed her and the class is not very difficult
Wouldn't recommend her. She's a hard grader and isn't very helpful outside of class. Not a very friendly, bubbly teacher. She assigns a lot of projects and assignments.
She speaks quietly, but as long as you pay attention and study, the class is easy.
She's okay. She's an easy grader, but I honestly did't like her. She can be really intimidating and I don't like that when I speak Spanish. She also gives a lot of projects.
I do not like the way she teaches at all.  I am a Spanish major and I'm failing her class.  She is an extremely difficult grader and I have yet to receive a decent grade on a paper.
She is very funny and very helpful! If you have the chance to take her for spanish 300 definitely do!

I really enjoyed having Dr. Scolere! She was very organized and class expectations were clear. I thought the class content was interesting, and INTD110 looks at some of the less thought of aspects of interior design. There is a big group project, but I thought it was manageable and she will work with you if there are problems with your group.

Dr. Scolere listens to her students. She received feedback that there was a lot of writing, so she chose not to assign the final paper. She truly cares about her students. Go to office hours and build a relationship w/ her, she gives great advice & is super helpful. Lots of extra credit, clear grading criteria, & super thorough feedback.

Lectures are like ted talks. She is excited about what she speaks about and is always put together. You don't have to take notes unless you want to. If you show up and pay attention it is designed to get an A. Group projects were frustrating. Go into her office hours and form a relationship with her and she will be more understanding.

Leah was an amazing professor. Her presentations are impeccable and you can tell she has tons of experience. Her studio was by far my favorite and I feel like I actually improved a lot with InDesign and layout. She's also super personable and is alway available to help!

She assigns A LOT of stuff for you to do outside of classes, and if you're not an Interior student, this class doesn't give you much information about the starters of interior design. So many group projects, which gets annoying. Her lectures are okay, she speaks as if you're listening to a TED talk so, if you like that then you should be good.

Not a good teacher at all didnt respond ever to any emails. Grades hard with no explanation and never showed how to do things she tested us on. Lectures sucked unless you like listening to someone talk for an hour on stuff she didnt even know her self. And got pissed at students because they asked for clarification more then once.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--Tough grader

comment: Dr. V is an amazing professor! Her HONR193 class is so interesting and I highly recommend it. She genuinely cares about her students and makes an effort to make class fun. I learned so much in her class and I would definitely take her again. You do a lot of discussions, but they are in small groups so it is not intimidating to share your thoughts.

I am a sophmore and have had honors seminars with Nicole for the past 3 semesters. She is by far my favorite professor that I have had at CSU. She is the most caring and understanding professor. She assigns long readings, but the seminars are always laid back and fun. Would highly recommend taking her classes if you are able to.

Dr. Viera's class on Wildlife is very interesting and along the way she helps you to develop your writing skills. Do the readings, participate in class, and you're golden! I would definitely recommend Dr. Viera to anyone. It's very obvious that she likes what she's doing and cares for her students.

I LOVE DR. VIEIRA! There's a lot of discussion and reading in the class, so you have to participate to do well, but as long as you put in effort and show interest she automatically curves/adjusts weights however she needs to get everyone an A. Best sense of humor I've seen, and she's got a very eccentric personality. 10/10 recommend.

Nicole is not only the chillest and entertaining professor ever, every lecture was fun and relaxed. She is also an excellent editor and gives great feedback on our papers. She is a MUST HAVE professor!

Nicole is a great professor. I had the pleasure of being the first freshmen seminar she taught & it was a blast. Participation and group discussion is the majority of the classes, and in order to participate I highly recommend at least skimming texts and taking notes to use in discussion. She will try to hold discussions outside if possible! :)

I absolutely love Nicole! She's incredibly understanding and such a nice person. She makes it easy to talk to her and feel comfortable with asking her any questions you have. If you have the chance to take her do it! She's one of my favorite teachers I've ever had

Overall, I liked Dr. Tucker. She has an easy to understand teaching style and is direct and to the point. She really tries to make her lectures fun, but lets be honest CHEM 113 is just not going to be the most exciting class ever. I recommend really trying to do well on the first few exams, as they get progressively harder over the semester.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Test heavy--Clear grading criteria

comment: While a lot of people don't seem to like Dr. Tucker, the way she explains things works really well for me. You do have to put in work for this class and won't do well if you don't show up or get behind, but the people who put in time seem to do better. Not at all condescending in her explanations (would explain 2+2 if you needed help with that).

I respect Dr. Tucker a lot and believe she is really intelligent, but the online structure of this class did not work for me. The office hours were essentially a repeat of the lecture videos given, and it would've been beneficial to use the office hours as problem practice and review instead.

I took this class with professor tucker years ago where I got my first C EVER. Professor tucker did not set you up for success. She lectures without making sure people understand. She does not teach, she announces. Her tests had questions that were NEVER covered in class or in the book. DO NOT take this professor!!

I took this course virtually and I have to say the class itself was extremely disorganized. To do well in this class you must stay on top of homework and study as much as possible. ratingTags: Lots of homework--Get ready to read--Test heavy

comment: I love chemistry. At least I loved chemistry. This class made me drop my pre-vet track, maybe I just cant do chemistry online. But the lectures didnt match what was on the exam, and theres TONS of homework that you HAVE to stay on top of. I did fine in the class but good god dont take this class while its online.

I believe Tucker was a MUCH better professor in person than online. Unfortunately, she has put little to no effort into putting this course together for an online format. Lectures are all prerecorded and blurry from last year, quizzes are prewritten from last year (very confusing), and there is very little test help or prep. Very disappointing.
She has no idea how to teach. Nothing on the exams was explained in lecture. Exams do not represent the lecture material. She speaks like we are all chem majors and know what she is talking about.

CSU's Chem department sucks, but Dr. Tucker herself really helps to lessen that feeling. There is a lot of work and material to be done and learn, but she makes it interesting. She's the best professor I've had for chem at CSU yet. I wish she taught higher level chem. She gives you what you need to succeed.

comment: This is a very difficult class but Dr. Tucker made it a little easier. She's definitely passionate about the material and wants us to succeed. Chem is hard, but Dr. Tucker is an amazing communicator. She lectures with enthusiasm and always speaks clearly. Watch her lectures, and you will have no problem in the class. 10/10 would take again.

The chemistry department at CSU sucks - the class itself is hard and lots of homework. But Dr Tucker makes it much better - definitely the best professor for any chem class at CSU. The lectures are engaging and she's always willing to help.

comment: The material is dry, but she explains it with enthusiasm. CHEM113 is difficult (a weed-out), and to succeed you need to show up, do the work, ask questions, and study. This professor gives you all the tools to succeed and teaches well, and I respect her for it.
Freshman weedout class plain and simple. Not there to help or teach just burn people out.

comment: Very tough, overloads you with homework and tests are difficult. Plus you get to take an exam every 3 weeks, fun...

ruth tucker is the worst. she is so confusing and babbles on about irrelevant things. she is no help to those who are struggling and is mean when confronted. do not take this class with her. (just avoid taking chem at CSU if you can)

Dr. Tucker is a sweet lady but I have not learned much in her class. The way the material is taught is confusing , which makes homework and studying for exams frustrating, Might as wee give my tuition money towards the TAs or student tutors.

comment: Although chem is a tough class and all the chem classes have the same homework requirements, she makes it fun and Intresting in lecture and shes always available for office hours and emails back very quick.

comment: Very quirky and funny

comment: Care about the material.

comment: Dr. Tucker's enthusiasm for chemistry made it way easier to make myself go to class-- something that everyone should do for general chemistry. Tucker has been my favorite professor so far. She is a genius and loves what she does. She does demos almost every class and makes every day interesting. Dr. Tucker is very enthusiastic about teaching and tries her best to keep chemistry entertaining and interesting. Tests are tough, but that wont change with what professor you have.

She is a great teacher. You do have to work for your grade but as long as you show up to class and pay attention then you should be fine. This is a hard class purely because it is a weed out class. If you need help be sure to go to office hours. She is by far one of my favorite teachers.

Professor Tucker has a passion for chemistry and she works hard to give her students all the information they need to succeed. Highly recommended, amazing teacher

gives lots of busy work and tests way harder than any work in class

great professor, she really knows the material and is tremendous at relaying that information to her students. as long as you put effort into her class, you might learn a thing or two

not bad but could be better

Mitch Combs is an amazing professor. He does everything possible to make the class comfortable, interesting, and engaging. The professor is really caring and understanding about medical situations and stuff. He is really helpful in class and outside of class as well. He also gives a lot of resources to help you succeed. ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Accessible outside class--Amazing lectures

comment: Dr. Bandar is a great professor. I had him in spring of 2020 so half of the class was virtual. The in person lectures were great. He posts good optional worksheets with keys

If you are interested to sign up for a class that has a professor who is very socially awkward and thinks that giving out partial credit is too much work, be my guest. If you contemplate talking to him about giving you more credit, there will be no luck there. You will STRUGGLE.

comment: Falene clearly loves what she teaches, which makes lectures barely feel like schoolwork. The lectures are helpful for doing the class work, and the homework is reasonably challenging. This was a fun class!

comment: She is very passionate about the subject but she interjects too many of her personal views into the class discussions and course material. Didn't bother to learn anyone's name except for the few students that speak the most, even though the class was only 15-20 people.

comment: My problem with Allison is not her teaching style; that is OK. The real issue with this professor is that she is very unfriendly. The class I took heavily focused on discussion and team dynamics, so be prepared to talk and ask questions if you want a good grade/get the most out of it.

Professor Albert is by far one of the best professors CSU has to offer. From day 1 she showed her love for not only the content of the class, but also her care and genuine interest in students. She is not only a great teacher, but an inspiration. Her class is not an easy A--you need to put the work in, study hard and pay attention in her lectures.

Lumina actively engages with course material and lectures are set up to ensure student success. As long as you put forth the effort to review material and pay attention you should do well. Professor Albert is one of my favorite professors I have had at CSU. She really cares about her students and their success in their professional careers. Lumina is a fantastic teacher. The guest speakers hosted in our classes were very impressive and added greatly to my experience! I highly reccommend taking any class she offers.

Lumina gives great feedback and uses relevant content. She communicates well and cares for her students. Also brings in great guest speakers with real life experience.

Lumina is an awesome prof! She communicates well and makes sure her lectures are thorough. She always brings in great guest speakers throughout the semester. As long as you are committed, hard working, and present/participate in her class, you will do good and enjoy her class!

Since the class is all about teams and groups expect a lot of teamwork. Put in good effort in the class and you will do great. Lumina is a great professor that cares about her students a lot. She will bring in great guest speakers, that are very inspirational.

Professor Albert is the most caring, down to earth, and passionate individual I have ever met. Great professor! Very passionate about teaching and business. She grades assignments and presentations relatively easy but not tests, which is fine. Class had very few assignments and points so every point mattered. Treat with respect and she'll treat you with respect.

Lumina is amazing. She cares about the success of her students so much. She brings in a lot of wonderful guest speakers and makes the class a fun and safe environment. She is by far my favorite professor Ive had.
Lumina is one of the most caring professors I've had. She is incredibly understanding and wants to help, so let her know what's going on in your life and get to know her outside of class.

Looking back on all of the great professors at CSU, Lumina stands out as one of the most knowledgeable and influential. Lumina is a professor who is there to help YOU, and she makes that clear from the first day of class. It's a class that you want and need to take seriously. Lumina is honestly my favorite professor I've ever had withinfive years of undergrad. comment: Lumina was  wonderful, and very upbeat all semester. She has a great love for life and the subjects she teaches. I would highly reccomend her as a teacher. comment: Pro Albert is a great teacher and she is passionate about what she teaches. You can learn a lot from real-life examples and her optimistic attitude. Professor Lumina is a wonderful, caring person. She has a deep passion for learning and is very affable. She cares deeply for her students and wants them all to succeed. The class was fantastic and I gained some very applicable knowledge.

Lumina is an amazing teacher! You can tell that she is very passionate in what she teaches. Lumina is my favorite teacher at CSU! She does a great job at teaching! Her lectures are intriguing and help you shape your own view on the world. She is the greatest teacher I ever have! She cares about students and really want help them do better in the class. Class participated needed, she  loves students share their experience and comments. Debra is very nice. Her class was also simple and effective for the online semester.
Professor Walker is absolutely amazing! She works really well with student with disabilities and her class is structured in a way that is very obtainable. She truly cares about the students success.

comment: Mrs. Walker is one of the nicest professors on campus. She has a smile on her face every morning and makes you want to do a good job! comment: Mrs. Walker is a great teacher who cares about her students. There are quizzes but she tells you what the quizzes will be on and are fairly easy. She has been my favorite teacher at CSU!

comment: Professor Walker is clearly inspired and knowledgeable about what she is teaching. Traveling through time via humanities was really intriguing. Very kind and out-going.

comment: I love her and she is one of my favorite professors ever. She is so nice, caring, and accommodating. She will help you the best she can and is always there to talk. Some reading and a few quizzes but they are super easy. I definitely recommend taking her class!!

you need to attend class because she takes points away if you don't and takes roll every class. you'll buy a 1000 page lit book and read most of it. in class tests. no homework besides the reading she assigns. very little work graded on, but if you dont read than you might get lost.

A very good professor, very chill. She assigns reading but usually goes over them in class so the tests are easy if you go to class and pay attention to what she talks about.

Jeff is the best! I took three of his classes and I have never regretted it! Jeff really cares about his students and gives ample time to do the assigned work. Clear grading and manageable tasks!

Jeff is the best! He is caring and his lectures are interesting. The work he assigns is doable and clear.
he is awesome!! definitely recommend taking a class with him!! Do your work, ask for help if you need it, and you will get an A easily.

comment: Prof Nowacki is a funny, kind man who keeps his students engaged, even online. He responds to emails quickly and gives insightful feedback. comment: super easy class to pass with an A if you just show up. He offers many extra credit opportunities and the work load is very minimal.

comment: Overall a nice guy but the lectures are very boring, he basically reads off his slides which are posted online. comment: He expects you to do the reading assigned so in class it is more of a lecture reviewing what the reading was. comment: If you do all the assignments to the best of your ability, it is extremely easy to pass.
I LOVE Dr. Harvey! You will not regret taking her class. She is incredible!

I LOVE Dr. Harvey. She is by far my favorite professor at CSU and I make sure to take any class I can with her. Her lectures are actually interesting and she explains things very well. Ashley was my favorite professor and I think everyone who takes her classes loves her! She is amazing and I truly enjoyed her lectures. As long as you stay on top of things in this class, you will get an A. I would 100% take this class again!
Dr. Harvey teaches 332 very well. She gives a lot of opportunities for extra credit. She is very understanding and makes lectures interactive and fun
She cares a lot about her students. Gives lots of extra credit opportunities. I love her teaching style

I took Hdfs101 with Harvey and shes so quirky and fun. I did find myself fall asleep in one or two classes just because it felt like the class was moving slow. Neverthelsss, its an easy class. Gives lots of extra credit opportunities. Uses iClicker in class for participation.

Dr. Harvey is an amazing professor with immense knowledge in terms of Death, Dying, and Grief. This course makes you vulnerable, Professor Harvey makes it an open and safe environment. Dr. Harvey is an incredible professor. She cares about her students and wants them to succeed. Clicker points are counted daily, but she also drops points at the end. This was by far the easiest class I have taken at CSU. The papers and simulations are super easy. 10/10!

Dr. Harvey is the sweetest prof. She shares sweet stories about her and her family. Her lectures are informative and easy to follow. She does do daily participation. Dr. Harvey is a sweet lady. The only issue I had with this class was the virtual child simulation. In this class, there is (or what feels like) a lot of busy work. Dr. Harvey is one of my favorite professors at CSU and is very passionate about any class she teaches. She gives a LOT of extra credit and does iClickers everyday so participation helps out. Exams are a bit difficult but you just need to apply the time and study. Small group work and one presentation that is also really easy.

Dr. Harvey is awesome! Just show up to class and do the assigned homework and you will pass. There is also a group presentation towards the end of the semester

She is a very sweet and caring professor. She is very educated in her work and really knows what she's talking about. She makes lectures fun by making them personal and she just wants you to do your best. She wants to see her students pass and she understands that we are all stressed college students. Very understanding as well.

I've had professor Harvey several times, each class she is very passionate about and will take the time to talk with you if needed. Gives you plenty of opportunities to earn points, test are difficult so dedicate time to study.
Really great teacher, didn't study much for tests but showed up to class everyday and passed with an A.
Harvey is a very sweet and caring professor! Very interesting and easy course and tons of extra credit opportunity. Highly recommend.
literally best teacher. she's so engaging and the class is super easy to follow. lots of life skills and if you take PSY100 things overlap so its super easy
My favorite professor at CSU. Iv'e taken 3 of her courses and have enjoyed all of them.  as long as you go to class you'll have no problem passing.

Fairly easy course. If you come to class and pay attention you will do well. Dr Harvey is very knowledgeable and cares about her students and wants them to succeed. She also gives quite a bit of extra credit!
She's nice, not a tough class. It's a great AUCC

LOVE LOVE LOVE her. She's so sweet and willing to help with anything at all. Her lectures were always fun and engaging because she'd use examples of her children and past experiences, which I loved. Sweetest professor ever
Dr. Harvey is an amazing professor! I really enjoyed coming to class because her lectures were always very fun and interesting!

Such a nice lady! I had such a good experience in this class, it lead me to exploring HDFS and that's what I ultimately declared. She is an amazing professor, and the class was set up really nicely. I loved having her!! She knew what she was talking about, and was willing to clarify any questions that you had about the material. She is an incredibly nice teacher who really just wants the best for her students. If you show up to class for the participation  you'll get a good grade in the class because the tests are extremely easy. Easy A class.

Dr. Harvey makes class fun and enjoyable. I didn't ever want to miss class.

The class was pretty easy and she is really nice. She really just read off of the powerpoint which she also posted online. I didn't really go to class often because of this. She does do some class participation points sometimes though.

I love love love Dr. Harvey. Definitely go to class, and you will pass. She is so easy to listen to in lecture, her classes are very interesting and provide great specific information. Love her.
Doctor Harvey was a really good professor for HDFS 101.  The class is very easy to pass as long as you pay attention.
Great teacher. Best to take class with friends, because there are group projects

She is so great! Very personable and interested in students and what they have to say. Class is very easy and fun. Her class made me confident in making HDFS my major. I would recommend this class to anyone.
She knows the material quite well and even includes personal experiences to help us learn! Not to mention she's cute.

She is super easy and I shouldn't complain but it was almost as if she was treating us all like high schoolers. It kind of annoyed me. Overall the class is easy and the text is interesting. Ashley is a GREAT teacher! She hands out points like there's no tomorrow. She is super helpful, a great lecturer and such a sweet heart!
Great Professor, very helpful, knew he info
Awesome teacher!

Such a great professor. Very helpful, and relatable. Uses her real life examples often which make things understandable. Slide notes are not very good, taking your own notes as well as using hers helps a lot.
one of the sweetest ladies i have ever met. her study guides are very helpful and explains all of her assignments in depth. extremely helpful teacher
She is a great teacher! She enjoys teaching the subject and she often relates the material to her own experiences. This is my favorite class this semester.

comment: KuoRay is awesome! He genuinely cares about his students and he takes the time to engaged with his students and make sure they are following along with his lecture.

Awesome professor. Great steal for csu

Dr. Brady is great. This class wasn't that hard either. Would definitely not take the class if you don't go.

comment: If you have Dr. Dewey, make sure you show up to class because not everything she says is on her slides, and often times that's the information tested on the exams. She posts the slides on Canvas, but you'll understand the material better if you show up to class. She is also very confusing, so going to office hours was helpful for me.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: I enjoyed Dr. Dewey's class, and I found that for the most part all I needed to do to do well was show up to class and take notes. I think she graded fairly and sometimes was pretty lenient, since she allowed us to make up some points on our exams via online quizzes. The couple times I spoke to her she was very kind and helpful.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Clear grading criteria

comment: Professor Dewey's LIFE102 class is heavily based on going to class and paying attention to what she specifically says because she doesn't post the powerpoints online. The powerpoints are VERY boring. MANY iClicker questions & weekly quizzes. Doesn't answer questions that students ask and typically ignores them. Basically have to teach yourself!
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Dr. Dewey seemed knowledgeable, but I didn't like her class. Her PP slides were really hard to work with and test questions are poorly worded, she's a "choose the best answer" kind of exam writer. She also doesn't communicate well in lecture, so you have to put in extra work studying outside of class if this isn't a subject you're comfortable with.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Clear grading criteria

comment: Dewey has the worst PP slides of any professor I've had, w/ very little to no information on each slide. It is almost impossible to study the necessary material for tests considering lectures are not recorded either. She is very intelligent but has great difficultly with clear communication. On top of all that, her test questions are ambiguous af.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Prof. Dewey gives decent lectures not very interesting and the Clicker questions are helpful exam practice. However her exam questions are poorly worded, obscure and often feel like she gives trick questions even though the material is supposed to be VERY straightforward. She somehow makes a very interesting subject very boring:(
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Sometimes when she asks questions or the questions she has on test can be worded a little awkward and/or you cant tell what she is getting at but if you ask her to explain it so you can understand what its asking she will. Shes nice but her slides dont have all the information on them so you have to go to class and listen to what she says.
ratingTags: Clear grading criteria--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: I accidentally slept through an exam & she was really understanding about it. She even gave me a cookie. Shes a great teacher and really cool if you get to know her.
ratingTags: ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Clear grading criteria--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: I really liked Dr. Dewey. She explained the topics well and was extremely helpful in office hours. I recommend asking for help when you get stuck because she really does care. I felt like her section on genetics especially prepared me for upper level classes in Biology. Not a book heavy class.

Study guides? "I don't have time to make those for you guys". So apparently a very loose list of topics is good enough. Not sure if she has tenure but my goodness, she was just terrible to have. Talked off the slides. Oh you had a question? Im just gonna dance around it but never truly answer. She didn't answer one question of mine concisely ever.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--Tests are tough

comment: If you go to class and pay attention you should do pretty well in the class. I think that having Neuwald first was bad because she was amazing and then going to Dewey was strange. She knows what she is talking about, but her lectures are long and boring but if you love biology you should do fine in her class. Basically AP Bio all over again
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Tests are tough--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Her voice is boring and whispery. Her slides suck. She doesn't take criteria well.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Tests are tough--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Shes actually a gr8 prof if you come to class and pay attention
Extremely hard to understand. I personally liked her better than Neuwald but I think that was because I liked the topics more and not the teaching style. I did not grasp anything from this class.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Tests are tough--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: It is clear that Dr. Dewey knows a great deal about biology, but it is also clear that she has no business teaching any type of class. Her lectures and her powerpoints leave you more confused than when you entered class. The study guides she provides are nothing like the exams, and the exams are often based off of non relevant information she says.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY

comment: I would not recommend taking from Dr. Dewey. She explains things in a confusing way and then gets visibly frustrated when the class doesn't understand. She asks for feedback from the class and instead of taking suggestions under consideration, she defends her original decision. Don't take from her.

Tanya is an amazing biologist who I truly look up yo. She is unbelievably knowledgeable and is more than willing to help her students succeed. She expects a lot, and her tests are not the easiest, but if you take the class seriously you will succeed.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Caring--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Lectures were boring and unorganized.

Be ready  to literally record her lectures because you can read the book and copy down the slides, but if you missed that one sentence she said halfway through her lecture, then you might as well kiss those B's you were getting on tests goodbye.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: She is clearly knowledgeable about Biology, but doesn't know how to teach. Her powerpoints are so broad and uneasy to follow and she often disregards questions asked in class. I was confused the entire time she taught and I did not learn anything from her.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY

comment: There is no doubt in my mind that Dr. Dewey knows a ton about biology and evolutionary biology, but she falls short as a teacher. Dr. Dewey's slides were nearly impossible to follow, her exams were ridiculously tough, and she would often disregard students - at one point she told us she dumbed down the exam.  I recommend another professor.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY

comment: Attended almost every class. Did not learn a single thing.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--TEST HEAVY

comment: Life 102 was given this year by 2 professors that split the semester in half. Dewey covered the second half of the semester, and the class became significantly less tolerable when the switch occurred. Her lectures are unorganized, and although given in full to study with, contains barely any  information. She was confusing in delivery and content.

Avoid taking any class with Tanya Dewey at all costs. She is constantly behind on all her lectures and then speeds through everything she didn't have time to teach the day before a test. Her slides are extremely jumbled and she rants about things that have nothing to do with what is on the tests. Don't take this class if you don't have to.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Her lectures are so broad she assumes that we all know what she is talking about and does not connect the dots between any of the information. I will go back and read the book or watch a video on what we learned in class and it is astonishing how different the information is. You are so unclear on what to learn that you have no motivation at all.

Her lectures are all over the place. She skips over information quickly and just simply doesn't make sense in lecture. She reads directly off her slides and often doesn't add any more commentary to help you better understand. You have to go read the textbook if you want to understand anything.

Extremely disorganized, mumbles, terrible test writer.  Tanya is often behind in her course material because she seems to have so many announcements and other nonsense to talk about at the beginning of the class that typically doesn't state her first slide until 10 minutes in.  Lecture slides aren't posted until day of class.  All- around awful.
Terrible lectures. Not organized. Does not keep class focused, has to remind people to NOT talk.

Tanya is a super sweet lady and obviously loves biology , but she does't have a clue when it comes to teaching. Her power points are not well organized, along with her lectures. She says she doesn't teach from the book, but I used the book a lot to help with adding to her notes and to help teach my self what we were learning.
Overall her lectures are extremely long and her slides and notes are very disorganized. She is very unclear and will skip from topic one topic to another in the most random fashion.
Terrible teacher. The lectures were long and boring, If you don't pay attention you don't pass the class. I would recommend doing the online homework- it helps your grade a ton.
DO YOUR ONLINE HOMEWORK! She is not very good but she switched off with another professor who was a lot better.  Try your best to pay attention.

The first quarter of the semester was rough - it takes a while to get used to her speaking. Lectures are not particularly fun to listen to. However, this can be made up by utilizing the textbook and online homework assignments to gain extra understanding. Eventually she seems not as bad, but still, not my favorite.

I'm sure she's a nice lady and all but I'd rather watch paint dry than listen to her lectures. She includes paragraphs of information on the slides and only gives you about 30 seconds to try and scribble everything down. Tests are pretty hard and difficult to study for.

Ben turned a class that I was really looking forward to into the worst class I have taken in the CS dept. Total lack of explanations on what is expected of assignments and group projects. Little to no examples to help guide you. He was also TWO MONTHS behind on responding to emails. Stay away if you can, the headache is not worth it at all.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Group projects--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: This is undoubtly the worse class I have ever taken in my whole life. B. Say is a very nice guys but a awful instructor. We had no books, the lectures and zybooks covered very poorly the materials that are asked in the assignment and the TAs didn't post most of lab videos. We basically had to learn everything by ourselves.

He was one of three professors I had for this class and he was one of the better ones. He was really genuine and nice, and he cared about all of us. Really this is a pretty easy straightforward class. We had one quiz, one paper and a final. We had in-person class once a week where we did an activity, so go to class (your grade depends on it).

Class was tolerable until about halfway through the semester, when the pacing skyrocketed out of nowhere and all students were left scrambling for help. Particularly, the unit on the Fuel framework left everyone completely lost, and the bulk of work (term paper draft + web project milestone) forced work for other classes to go ignored. Avoid.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Get ready to read--Lecture heavy

comment: I took Ben last year and I occasionally read the reviews for him. I can tell you that some of the positive reviews on here are written by his TAs. This man has no business teaching anything related to computer science, and the school should quit promoting awful lazy teachers. If you are stuck with Ben fellow students, then find a YouTuber.

Took him during COVID. Constantly changed the due dates on his assignments without notifying students. Exams had no correlation with the homework, usually meaning if you wanted to do well you had to study a week or two ahead to catch up with what was actually being tested. Senior taking my capstone course, and this was somehow my hardest class :/

Ben is my favorite prof at CSU. I took his class as a freshman & had never coded, so it was hard. Looking back, it prepared me for majoring in CS well. The class offers tons of help from Ben and amazing TAs. The only reason why ben isn't rated better on here is cause 163 is not an easy A and coding can be frustrating when you first start.

Honestly, Say seems like a great person. Unfortunately, that does not translate to a good professor. Our midterm category is weighted at 60% of the final grade and the first midterm included content that ended up being introduced 2 entire weeks later. Luckily you can get weeks ahead on the work to be prepared for those incidents, shouldn't have to.

A computer science professor who is terrible with computers. Class is taught by TAs pretty much exclusively. He does everything last minute and isn't helpful when you ask for help or clarification. The tests and tricks in them to try and make you miss them. The course work and exams do not match up much, be prepared to study a ton on your own.

Ben does good lectures, but they were unnecessary for a B. Zybooks(the hw website) teaches you everything you need to know. Between the lab projects and Zybooks, you learn the material better than sitting in a lecture. The material builds on itself, so it's important to grasp each concept before moving on. TAs are available on Teams for help.

Ben refuses to explain the material or go over any relevant examples that would make the problems understandable. He intentionally tries to trick his students and is not of much help in office hours. I would avoid and try to get literally anybody else.

Benjamin Say seems like a nice guy. However, when it comes to your grade, being a kind individual does not benefit your grade. The class is very unorganized. With coding being a problematic language, Ben does not take any effort to give visual examples with codes. He expects you to read the textbook and fully understand. Avoid at all costs.
A horrible teacher, do no take him if you don't have to. Seems to despise his students, intentionally attempts to catch and fail students. Will try to trick you.

This is easily one of the worst professors I've had. It hurts to say it because he seems like a really cool professor and is pretty nice during the lectures. I also think his lectures can sometimes be fun, but most students would probably disagree. His tests are pretty hard compared to the content you are learning. If you can avoid him, please do.
He doesn't know what he is talking about ever. He doesn't care about his students and he should not be a teacher.

Ben Say is a very fun, easygoing teacher. He does grade tests very harshly, but they are not impossible. The only problem with Ben is that he doesn't understand the material. He was unable to demonstrate how to do problems in class and had to demontrate the problems during the next lecture when he had the premade notes another proffesor gave him.

Mr. Say is literally the nicest person you will ever meet, but I don't think he is the most engaging teacher. Most of the classes are him lecturing over a powerpoint and I personally had to do a lot of outside work to understand the concepts. To me, the class and department felt very unorganized.

Ben is friendly and knows the content well. It was difficult to keep up with note taking during lecture but I found out halfway through class that everything I was writing down is in the slides. There were lots of tests and they only had a couple questions so I had to study well because missing 1 or 2 questions had a big effect on my grade.
He is a really fun teacher and really knows what he is talking about. The information is presented in a very clear and entertaining manner.

He is a great teacher. It is clear he is passionate about CS. His lectures were great. The only thing to watch out for is that he doesn't offer clear details on homework but if you set up tests it shouldn't be a problem.

Jack is a horrible teacher I have never hated a class like I did his I would not recommend him. He is unforgiving and not helpful at all. I understand that this class might be a weed out class but cmon man, I pay to learn not to have some teacher get mad when you want to ask a stupid question which no question should be considered stupid.

Jack Applin was the worst teacher I've had honestly. The labs, quizzes, and exams are all doable although the questions on the quizzes and exams are tricks most of the time. The real rough part is the homework. I had a tutor for half of the semester helping me with the homework and I still got a 50% on most of them. The grading is obscure at best.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Tough grader

comment: Jack Applin is a snarky guy who cares very strongly about CS and making sure CSU is putting out good computer scientists. His class is something of a weed out course where if you're not committed enough to CS, then this might be where you'll stop. With that being said, he is a great teacher and really teaches you the material well.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Test heavy--Clear grading criteria

comment: I didn't have any troubles with the material. I am giving a bad rating because of how he teaches. He lectures in front of a chair covered with a my little pony towel. He impulsively and unnecessarily gives his opinion on politics and social issues. He makes frequent sexual/inappropriate references. He is unprofessional, and he alienates students.
Jack knows what he is talking about. Weekly quizzes are open note. Start the homework assignments early, rarely can they be started and completed on the same day.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Tough grader

comment: His attitude is poor about teaching and he's hostile unprovoked. Considering everything was online, you would think he or his TAs would respond more online. They didn't- you're on your own. He is the farthest from understanding if you reach out to him personally regarding literally anything.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Tough grader

comment: I would give Jack a zero if I could. Jack hands out zeros on assignments like Oprah hands out free stuff. You will consistently get zeros on technicalities. The content of the class itself isn't crazy difficult, but Jack's grading style turns A students to C students. Jack also has an extremely hostile attitude. Avoid him at all costs if possible.

Jack is disappointing. I came into the class expecting him to be tough, sarcastic, but also a great teacher. He is the first two, but definitely not the last. You cant mask pure dislike for students and teaching as sarcasm. He is a lazy professor, just reading slides. No wonder hes not in industry anymore, probably isnt welcome back...

Jack is very knowledgeable about programming. However, he is often demeaning to students that ask "dumb" questions. They may need help understanding, but he doesn't care. Instructions for assignment are often written with implicit rules that are only clear to advanced students and programmers. His tests are full of "trick" questions. Never again.

One of the most highly rated instructors in the CS department at CSU because of his knowledge and ability to make students learn. Prepare yourself for this class by putting on a tough skin and getting ready to work hard. Yes, Jack knows his stuff. Yes, Jack knows how to teach. But he's also the most sarcastic, intolerable professor I've had.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Lots of homework--Tough grader

comment: Jack is a great lecturer. He speaks clearly and his thoughts are organized. He is, however, a keyboard warrior. The class environment is hostile on the message board. The class is designed by Prof. Malaiya and it sucks but Jack's lectures make it slightly better.

Assignments aren't really hard, but Jack isn't very good with detail. You can follow the instructions and develop beyond the spec only to find that the entire thing is graded in a very particular and obscure interpretation of those instructions. Easy to get a 0 on working products. Note: many of these positive reviewers sound exactly like Jack....

Jack is alright. He's not a bad teacher, but he needs to tone his attitude down a bit. I personally thought the class was a cake walk and the homework assignments were a joke, but everyone else seems to disagree. My biggest complaints are his disrespectful comments and his attitude. Making fun of a student in front of 180 people is unprofessional.

If you like a professor with a constant stream of sassy remarks, Jack might be the man for you. But the homework is tough and the direction in how to do it can be vague. He likes to punish people with negative scores too, so beware. Sometimes his punishment seems vengeful; you can easily get a zero on a homework for a minuscule error.
Jack himself tends to speak without a filter but makes up for it with the exam curves. On some exams he curved them by over 20%. As long as you do your work in this class you'll pass just fine.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--TEST HEAVY

comment: makes lectures interesting and is somewhat funny. homework is long but reasonable and helps to understand the topics being covered in class. where he really goes wrong is his exams. he will test you over the most minuscule syntax and coding errors. it seems like 3/4 of his test is almost trick questions. The average on exams is always very low.

The class itself isn't too bad, but this isn't about the class. It's about the teacher, who is a sarcastic little old man. You may think his sarcasm is funny at first, but after a couple months of him giving rude sarcastic comments to your questions you'll be over it. Definitly not a good professor, and I would use more profanity to describe him.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--Hilarious

comment: I don't know why people are giving him low scores, he's my favorite professor I've had in my two years at CSU.

To pass this class you have to spend a good amount of time on the coding homework. They built on eachother so make sure it works and get help when you need it. The tests and quizzes aren't bad because he gives a generous curve but the homework will make or break you so prioritize it. This is not an easy class so only take it if you have to.

Applin is straight up hilarious. He's a tough teacher but extremely knowledgeable. If you don't put in effort to actually learn the material, you will not be happy with this class. However, his teaching style is perfect to learn the right mentality for Computer Science, and he makes you fully understand the material.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Clear grading criteria--Hilarious

comment: If you're not familiar with programming this class will be challenging. He is a really entertaining professor and keeps you engaged during class but it's really like learning another language and can be overwhelming for a 1 credit course. There should be an intro to these intro classes for non-CS majors.
I loves these classes. They were also really easy for me but that is because I am a CS major... They are probably the easiest three 1 Credit classes I will ever take!
If you are somewhat familiar with programming (i.e. can make a for loop in a certain language) this course is very easy.

I actually feel fortunate to have been taught by this professor. It could've been soo much worse and drier but he makes great metaphors to help solidify the information and he is very funny.  I had no prior programming experience. Therefor, the class was very difficult and demanding, yet I loved this class and will be sitting in on the others.

Applin is a quirky but great teacher. The 150 series is a great intro to Comp Sci, and is what made me add a CS minor. Homework can be hard and tricky but that's what computer science is all about. I highly recommend spending a good amount of time out of class practicing material. Nice to have a few short 5 week class!!

AVOID HIS CLASSES at all costs!  He is unhelpful, sarcastic, and a terrible instructor. The CS150 series are introductory courses to Unix & C programming and he managed to turn the HW into tricky CS riddles, at which he would often use CS tricks NOT taught in class in his solutions.  Also, working together on the HW is forbidden & dishonest.

Personally, he is my favorite professor ever, but it's all subjective, and about what works for you. His lectures are a dialog with himself, which makes it easier to pay attention than someone talking at you. About the complainers: they are apathetic newbies and the material is tougher than basket weaving, so they blame the teacher.

Fantastic professor if you're willing to work. If you're not, his classes are miserable. He's my favorite professor in CSU. Why? Because it's impossible to pass his classes without LEARNING THE MATERIAL. I work at Intel because of what he taught me.

This is a man who skims through vague slides and often directs students to use google rather than approach him for help. If you have no prior programming experience (like me before I took the course) it will be hell. Otherwise, I'm assuming the class is moderately easy and even enjoyable. Oh yes, and finals are worth 40% of your grade!

This is the first class I've had in a very long time that I actually dreaded going to. I didn't much care for his teaching style (skimming slides). Good luck getting help anything. I was told to "look it up" if I had questions. You are not even supposed to ask fellow students for help because that's "cheating".

FOR BEGINNING PROGRAMMERS: the homework starts easy, but when it gets harder, you'll struggle for help. the GTAs always told me to search Google or read the book for help, and Jack was rude. read everything, go to class, and pick up Java for Dummies or something. IF YOU HAVE EXPERIENCE: Jack teaches the class for people like you. you'll be fine.

Absolutely worse professor ever. Doesn't teach anything, hardly helps outside of class, worthless. Get programming for dummies and you will get way further than with this guy. He isn't even a professor, he just got fired from HP or something like that.

This professor does not teach he just reads the notes of last semester's teacher!!!!! It's ridiculous you need to know how to teach teach this class efficiently. On top of that, he totally ignores a majority of the students and focuses on the students that joke around with him! I know that's pretty harsh but I think that he just wasn't very helpful

This guy is a joke. He definitely had "holier than thou" attitude. He lectures were pointless and had trouble explaining to students that had questions. He assignments were vague at times and we never touched the book. You are better off looking commands up online and how to use them than asking the teacher or looking in the book.

I would have to agree with the student above, was useless and didn't care about the students at all. His TA that he had was even more useless. If you had any type of questions, the response you received was, look it up in the book. I don't imagine him being around too much longer. Take any other teacher is possible. He was funny though.

One of the worst teachers in the computer science department.  Completely unable to explain Unix to students who have no prior knowledge.  He was very preachy and had a "I art holier than thou" attitude the entire class.

Ben is by far the best writing teacher I have had. He really cares about his students and gives amazing feedback in every assignment no matter how large or small. I listened to him and his lessons and my writing improved so much. Trust the process! He is truly amazing and is flexible if you have a busy schedule.

Ben was flexible & accessible this fall20 sem. He was understanding of life stresses & gave opportunities to bring grades up through my work. It was important to watch the week modules to get due dates of discussion posts (etc) for the week. He gives lots of assignments to help w/ ur writing & ur research for the class. HIGHLY recommend!!!

G is the best choice for anyone who likes less busywork and cares about their future. The class is structured very well and communication with G is important for success. Some professors will not make arrangements, but G will. 4 absences, 1 sick day. about 20-30 mins hw daily. He's funny, grades semi-harshly, but you WILL improve with G. Fantastic.

I hate reading and writing so naturally I didnt enjoy this class. That being said, I can tell Ben does his best to try to make the most out of his class. There are lots of assignments but theyre all meaningful; theres no busywork. Youll get out of this class what you put into it. I learned a ton about writing that will help in the future.
ratingTags: Tough grader--Lots of homework--So many papers

comment: Ben is definitely a tough grader and makes you work for it, but he is a super nice guy and tries to make a boring class interesting and fun.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Inspirational--Tough grader

comment: Turned a relatively easy course into one of the most ridiculous courses I have ever taken. If you're looking to fulfill a simple AUCC credit ... STAY AWAY! Never ask for an extension b/c he may grant you an extra day but WILL add another assignment on top. Also, he disregards Letters of Support from the WGAC
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Skip class? You won't pass.--So many papers

comment: This teacher is a sad excuse of a person. Made the easies class I was taking a living hell. He does not know how to use canvas and is inconsistent when posting homework. Incredibly homework heavy with useless tasks that provide teachings of the same skills you learned in your 3rd-grade literacy class. DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS WITH BEN GREENLEE.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Tough grader

comment: I thought Ben was a super great professor; though the projects that we were given did require a lot of time and thought, I feel as though he grades very fairly. I always enjoyed what he had to say in class and the reading given for homework was always entertaining and kept me engrossed. I would absolutely take another class with him.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Participation matters

comment: He is a super nice guy, but a super tough grader. If you want a B or A in this class do not take this teacher.

Exam questions were written to trick you, not test your knowledge. Even if you knew the answer to the question, it was hard to tell what the professor wanted you to say. Multiple questions were marked as wrong in each exam, even if you got the right answer, and would only be corrected after multiple emails.

Didnt care at all about the students, she often refused to answer emails or direct students to TAs even if that student had no idea who their TA was. During the pandemic, she didnt care if a student was in their death bed, requiring them to come to class or find a way to prove that they were required to quarantine.

She started the semester off great. She responded to emails in a timely manner and her intro lecture seemed friendly. This was an online course so communication is MORE important. As the semester went on, she stopped responding to student emails even if the student was emailing about missed work due to COVID. Would not recommend her for online.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Graded by few things--Tough grader

comment: do not recommend. doesnt respond to emails. ignores her students (all of them, i would know because we have a groupme) super lecture heavy. at least 100 pages of notes every week, 50-100 pages of textbook readings, 4 hours of lecture videos. quizzes are misleading and she refuses to regrade even though we took answers straight from lecture slides.
ratingTags: Tough grader--Lecture heavy--Get ready to read

comment: Dr. Zhang's expectations were reasonable and he did a good job with helping us work through assignments. The workload was challenging but doable. He is a great guy with relevant practical knowledge and I would have loved to have this class in person!
Good class. No busy work. Learned a lot. Not a hard grader. Could imagine it would be better in person without Covid.

Stat is supposed to be a hard and dry topic. Jon was somehow able to gracefully turn the subject into an engaging and memorable experience with narratives and interesting applications. I've learned more from this one class than all of my quant classes combined in the past. Highly recommend!

Jon's fast-talking energy is great for a Monday morning class. He had great communication with the class and was extremely clear and approachable. He has a gift for making difficult concepts understandable.

AMAZING professor! Very intelligent and well-versed in diverse business disciplines. Lectures were engaging, fun, and packed with information. Broadened my horizon. Does not take attendance and does not use any textbook, you have to keep up with things and track deadlines on your own. Not a picky grader. If you worked at it, you will get an A.

Jon is a new marketing professor at CSU this year and spent years teaching at the University of Washington before. I've had the pleasure of taking my marketing capstone with him. His reviews from his previous job were amazing. One student mentioned, "True asset to UW, business education, and capitalism!" Now replace "UW" with "CSU"!

Bob is overall a great professor. There are times that things he says arent politically correct, but it is because he knows his audience. He is excellent at getting students involved with lectures. There are quite a few homework assignments and quizzes, but all are super short and painless. Take a class with him if you want to learn lots and laugh

This professor is high energy and has done some amazing stuff for the community but I find some of his comments discriminatory once in awhile. If you have to start a sentence with "I'm not trying to be racist but..." that makes the following statement still racist. He comes from a good place but needs to approach multicultural education differently
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Lecture heavy

comment: Excellent class, but Dr. Delmore definitely makes you work for your grade. Take good notes during lectures, attend class, and ask questions! Nice class to have in person.

Very funny prof, he is straight to the point and not afraid to step on a few toes. Participate!! Ask questions, give out opinions. He gives out incentives to those who do, from shot glasses to chicken socks. Do not say "What?". You will get corrected. Try "Pardon me, Dr Delmore?" Keeps class interesting.
He is very engaging as a lecturer. Students become part of his presentation.

I took two other Java programming courses and it never made any sense. Prof. Firooz's class is the first time it finally made sense. He does a great job explaining things and as long as you do the practice exercises he gives you'll be able to follow along fine.

Professor Firooz is the perfect instructor for this class! I don't have a business background and wasn't sure if I would do ok in a MBA program but professor Firooz explains everything so clearly and uses so much humor I never drifted off or got bored.

I was nervous about starting the MBA program but Professor Firooz was the perfect professor for my first class. He's extremely knowledgeable and his lectures are entertaining which makes it easier to pay attention in an online class. I would definitely take another class from him!

This was the first class I've taken where I can see actually using the information. Prof. Firooz has so much real world experience and he's super helpful with explaning things outside of class. Definitely take his class!

i have never had a professor like this before. He actually knows what he's talking about and he teaches based on real world situations. Even though i don't plan to go into sale i finally feel like i'm taking a class that i'll be able to use after graduating.

Jon is a fantastic professor. Really funny, keeps things moving so classes fly by, and you actually learn a ton of actually usefull stuff. He's always available if you have questions and really cares about students. Make sure you have him for your capstone!
really good teacher. don't take your marketing capstone with anyone else, you'll regret it.
