Easily the best professor I've had at CSU. This is the first class where I feel like I actually learned something that I can use in the real world. Classes fly by and are never boring.

Absolutely the best professor I've had at CSU! He really cares about his students and goes out of his way to help whether it's with homework, job advice, or personal issues. His classes are the only ones I can actually stay awake for and I actually learned something in his class.

One of my favorite professors. Genuinely cares about the students in his class and consistently makes time to provide resources that will help with projects. Case studies are interesting and offer good practice to apply to projects. Keeps lectures interesting and engaging, which is hard to do with a room full of graduating seniors

I had a strong A going into the final, which is technically the only exam. Well, I studied hard and finished with a B+. So use that as an indication of how tough it was graded. Comes off as arrogant and a know-it-all. Spent his entire career at HP so that's all he talks about.

Jon was hands down the best professor I've had in my entire experience at CSU. He genuinely cares about his students and their well being. He really values constructive feedback (to give and receive)and he goes out of his way to make lectures the best he possibly can for his students. Please visit his office hours and get to know him, he's awesome!
His Sales Management class was one of the only classes I was really impacted by throughout my CSU career. Highly recommended!

My favorite professor at CSU! Jon taught my marketing capstone class and taught us really valuable real world knowledge and prepared us well for life after graduation. He was a professor that I could go to for academic, professional, and personal advice. He had a positive impact on my college career by being helpful, kind, and knowledgeable.

Classically arrogant about his experience. He has a great work background but it seems he has quickly fallen into academia where his answers are the "right" answers.  He is very predictable in that he wants you to regurgitate his answers rather than teach/help you think and problem solve.  He always seems hurried too.

I really enjoyed his lectures.  He explained thoroughly and provided practical companies and situations for examples as well as his personal experiences.  Though he provided the lectures, Scott Kinner was the SC who graded our papers.  I'd say the class is great on a learning level and somewhat difficult in grading.  You'll have to really work hard

One of the best professors I've had at CSU.  He uses examples from his past which make it so much easier to understand the material and know why it actually matters.  He really cares about the students and making sure they do well.

The material and effort in this class is pretty low-grade (it's also a one credit class), but Jason is near-useless as a professor. Took a class with him during COVID, and he asked the students coming to in-person lectures to stop coming in because he did not want to come into class anymore. A solid example of how dedicated to teaching he is.

Courtenay is an AMAZING professor! She is one of the best professors that I have ever had. She cares about her students, always will work with you one-on-one if needed, and she makes sure you know your spanish and can communicate in an effective and coherent manner.
Supa nice prof makes sure you do well in class

I took this class spring term 2020 half in class and half online due to the coronavirus. This teacher made both in class and online classes very helpful towards assignments/quizzes/tests (nothing is ever left out). Participation is encouraged which can really help your spanish- creates a good learning environment within your class(no embarassment)
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Accessible outside class--Participation matters

comment: Her teaching style is unique (conversational), however, considering the level of the class, she expected too much. Instead of lectures or notes you only practice with other students. She is willing to work with you on late assignments but BEWARE I rarely knew when the assignments were due or how to do them. So you might be working with her a lot.
Professor Biser-Suarez is very kind and extremely helpful inside and outside of class. She gives really good feedback on papers and tests and makes Spanish grammar pretty easy to understand.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Participation matters--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS

comment: Dr. Rosenberg was mediocre at best. She had lack of personality, would not be completely helpful on her online lectures. Her notes and text-books she sent were not synchronous with her exams so it was hard to get a good/decent grade. Would not take again.

Dr. Rosenberg is relatively cold and expects a lot from you, but she truly does want her students to succeed. Do the extra credit assignments because they will boost your grade a ton, and be willing to put in the work because she notices who does. Tests are hard but not the worst, just make sure you know everything covered in the lab manual.

Dr Rosenberg isn't a very approachable person which is frustrating in a class where you have to ask for so much help. Her monotone voice and unorganized lectures make class hard to handle, but most people I know will agree that she's better than the other professor who teaches this course.

She isn't a horrible teacher. She is there when you need help in the lab. There is a ton of busy work that doesn't help you with her test. You can answer most of the lab report questions without doing the lab but they won't help you on the test. Her test is horribly hard and not representative of the class.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--EXTRA CREDIT--Tests are tough

comment: Very helpful, gives extra credit, and understanding. She is monotoned so it is hard to stay interested and focused. She goes off of power points, mainly covering the chapter. The test questions are not on study guides but sometimes taken from the end of the chapter.

He's a nice guy who keeps class entertaining, but it was tough to keep up. Sometimes he'd forget to explain things in class, and leave students floundering during assignments or test. This was online, however, not sure how it is in a normal year.

A nice guy, but wasn't helpful at all. His lectures, and the class as a whole, convey little useful information. He often spends the majority of class talking about his research or random wildlife management efforts that don't pertain at all to quiz/exam material.

Having taken a tough chemistry course in high school, this class was a breeze. I had little to no problems on tests or exams. Even if it's your first time, she explains things very well and at a great pace. There are quite a few assignments, however.

this was hard because its chem, not cause of the prof. if you take notes while doing the homework, you don't have to watch the lectures, but they're there if you need help. lots of office hours and you can tell she cares. let us all do a test retake once. just take notes and do the hw and you get a B at least.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Dr. Mies knows her stuff but if you don't understand something the first time she explains it, you're screwed. She asks students to be patient with her given the circumstances covid has created, but refuses to do the same for students. Given it is a 100 level course, the test material is far too advanced especially considering homework content
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Get ready to read--Test heavy

comment: One of those teachers that thinks the only class you're taking is theirs. You'll have to dedicate all your time in the week to this class at the expense of your other classes if you want that A. Lots of exams and constant homework assignments that use the Mcgraw connect which is awful. No extra credit offered so if you bomb an exam, that's it.

I did not at all like this class, but I have nothing against Dr. Mies. She really did try to make the class better for us, but learning chem online combined with online college was not easy. She doesn't give very much feedback but she's provided us with plenty of resources to use. Overall, bad class but a good professor.

I love Dr. Mies, she's very passionate about her teachings and she's very helpful during office hours. Her material is hard but it makes you think. ALEKS is the worst, there are clicker points. Read and study the material and you'll be fine.

Dr. Mies is a great professor and explains the material in a clear and concise way. She is extremely helpful and patient during office hours and never makes you feel dumb for not understanding certain concepts. I was nervous about this class in the beginning, but ended up really loving chemistry!
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Lecture heavy

comment: Kassy Mies is an amazing professor! Chem is a tough subject, but she makes everything easy to understand, and doesn't move too fast. She is hilarious, and her lectures were always entertaining. Her exam questions are also really fair. Even with covid-19, she was accessible and flexible to students who needed help.

I'm bad at chemistry, but Dr. Mies made me better at it. I wish she could've been there for other hellish classes like geometry. Her lectures help way more than the online textbook. GO TO CLASS THE DAY BEFORE EXAMS IT HELPS SO MUCH. I didn't have any problems with her or with course materials when COVID struck, so I can't comment on that.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Caring

comment: Is not understanding to students and the difficulties that may be faced during times of hardship (covid-19).

She is a nice lady, but she says she cares about her students but its not true. I knew some people that got logged off during their exams and that she never tried to help them. She wouldnt let them log back in or anything, they just got the grade they got and thats it. Also the homework load is outrageous. Only take her if you are ready for it.

Professor Mies lectures well, but doesn't seem to understand how to put together a coherent and intelligible video lecture to save her life. Her homework is three times that of hard science courses at the three hundred level. Save your tutition and take chemistry somewhere else, and not in a class of 300 with three hours of homework a night.

I had Dr. Mies for Gen Chem 1 and 2, and she was amazing! She's so caring and her lectures were so organized. If you go to her lectures, take notes, and do the homework, you will learn everything you need to know and do well in the class. The way homework is structured is confusing and overwhelming at first, but totally doable

Her online teaching is the worst of any professor Ive had. She assigns reading and homework and then has an exam. There is no actual instruction or teaching from her. Also, I tried reaching out to her multiple times and she constantly blew me off.

Mies is a solid choice for a general chemistry professor. She's personable. She is patient and genuinely cares about her students learning. All the general chemistry classes are all structured to have a lot of homework, which is kinda annoying and the softwares are tedious. I mostly did homework in class. The exams can be hard if you don't study.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Participation matters--Clear grading criteria

comment: Dr. Mies is one of my favorite professors I have had. Chem is a tough subject but the way she explains it makes so much more sense than the textbook. I would highly recommend attending her lectures. She moves at a slow pace which helps a lot. If you're taking chem definitely take her section. There's a ton of homework but dont skip any of it.

Dr. Mies is a spectacular professor. She does such a great job at explaining the concepts of chemistry. Im so glad I had her as my professor because chem is such a difficult topic and she made it really easy to understand. Shes very sweet and energetic that shes makes you excited to learn chemistry
Dr. Mies is one of the best chemistry professors in the department. She explains the material very well and goes at a good pace.

Kassy is an AMAZING professor! If you get the chance to take her, do it. Classes are homework heavy however, it is just the nature of the program and not the professor. Kassy is an extremely caring and passionate professor and cares deeply for her students. The class can be challenging but it will make you better for it. By far the best chem prof
Dr Mies clearly loves to teach, and shows up every day with a lot of energy. She also explains everything really clearly, and is great about answering questions.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Caring

comment: Highly recommend! Engaging lecturer, answers questions concisely and with excellent illustration. Breaks down the math required, making it easy to understand, so definitely choose her if you struggle in this area. Engaging, wonderful person! Cares about her student's success! Weather resulted in us getting behind in lecture. Not her fault.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--Amazing lectures

comment: Does not get through entire lecture slide shows, so she falls behind the other classes and does not go over everything that will be on the test. She spends 20 minutes on one clicker question.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Literally the best professor I have ever had. If you've never take Chemistry before she is the best professor for you. She went out of her way to help me on multiple occasions. She truly cares about her class, she is funny, she holds the classes attention, I just cant say enough good things about her. She slowly walks through equations too!

Professor Mies is my favorite professor here at CSU. She is an excellent lecturer and is very helpful in office hours. She takes her time teaching the material so you understand everything while still being diligent in getting everything done. She makes it easy to pay attention to chemistry, which can be a boring subject.
ratingTags: Respected--Accessible outside class--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: She's as good as it gets for a chem professor. Take her if you get the chance.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--Amazing lectures

comment: Chem 113 is a very hard class coming out of Chem 111 which was very easy. Mies does a good job but sometimes she is hard to follow. Be ready to work for this class no matter the teacher
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Caring

comment: Breaks down concepts to the most basic of levels, especially math.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: General chemistry is a hard subject but professor Mies made it so much easier to understand than I would've thought. The class has a lot of online problems that you need to do to succeed, but it makes really good practice. They also post practice tests before every exam that are super similar, so I'd recommend doing those.
ratingTags: Respected--Skip class? You won't pass.--Clear grading criteria

comment: Chemistry is already a hard subject, but Dr. Mies is the best professor at CSU for gen chem. She explains a lot in lecture and has a lot of examples that are clear to understand, and if you do not understand something she will take time in or out of class to explain it. I had another prof for chem before her and switching saved my grade.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Amazing lectures--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Homework is absolutely necessary to do well. The homework and readings are where the information will be taught. The lectures will not teach the content but will help explain any additional details or questions. Lots of content to cover, but as long as you stay on top of the work it isn't too bad. As a plus, there's lots of extra credit.

Dr. Mies is super nice but her teaching style is a little different than some people might be used to. She doesn't really stop to explain anything she just goes quickly through it so if you don't understand something ask questions! Clicker points every day so make sure to go to class. The tests are fairly difficult so study a lot
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: A wonderful instructor. She is concise, detailed and interesting. She presents the material in a way you can easily comprehend it, even if you have never taken a previous chemistry course.
She was fair and understood we are human and make mistakes. she also explained things well.

Dr. Mies is a great professor. I had her for chem 181, and then 111 and 113. She explains things really well, and really knows her stuff. I recommend her for any gen chem class at CSU! Overall great professor. Its not her fault the chem department sucks!

She explains things so well! I had a terrible Gen Chem 1 teacher and she explained things so well and even filled in the spaces I missed. She is a truly great professor. She does put the lectures online, but there is clicker questions. I never used the textbook.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Hilarious--Amazing lectures

comment: Dr. Mies is amazing!! Adore her.

I really like Dr. Mies. She seemed a little crunched for time, but did a great job on making sure we understood what she was saying. If we didn't cover it, she didn't test us on it. 10/10, would take class again (If for whatever reason I had to...)

I had Mies for pre-gen chem and she is really knowledgeable on the subject of chemistry. Her lectures were very precise and not that boring; her slide shows always displayed the main point of the lecture. I liked her so much that I signed up for her gen chem course next semester

Dont listen to these ratings. She doesnt grade rude as you literally get to choose how she grades. Yes, the class is difficult, but it is also beneficial. If you put in the work and listen to the feedback, you will do fine. Its also a required course for business, so you will have to take the class.

Dont listen to any of these reviews. BUS 300 is required for the business school. My experience with Jenny was great, and I never had any problems with her grading. Also, for the people saying her grading was rude, you literally get to choose how she grades you. Yes, the class is pretty difficult, but it will better develop your writing.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Lots of homework--Tough grader

comment: She's a REALLY harsh grader, most of the way she grades is very subjective. She makes this class excessively hard for no reason at all. Do NOT take this class with her, seriously.

This is one of the worst graders Ive ever experienced. She made an easy class hard for no reason. Plus, in times like this were people are literally dying, she is not lenient AT ALL! Her feedback is not useful, and kinda rude too. The class is useful for the future but dont take it with her. It feels more like a grading than a learning class lol.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Get ready to read--Tough grader

comment: "Dr." Jenny Morse gives you 4-8 assignments per week, with half of them being nowhere accessible online, and she will send you into assignments with no instruction. She makes this the hardest class in the COB by far, if you do not like untransparent teachers who give no explanation, do not take Jenny! Best of luck if youre forced into her class.

Jenny is a tough grader and doesnt give enough information on assignments. Since classes were switched online this semester, shes given a lot more work and counts off for small errors. Very meticulous grader. If there is another professor for this class, take it with them.

Many complain about Dr. Morse's grading, but if you actually work hard and try to understand the class there doesn't seem to be much of a problem. The point of the class is that the little things are what will stand out to professionals. There is a group project that takes up the last two months. The criteria for it was not very clear.

Dr. Morse is one of the best professors I have had at CSU. I have learned so much from her and she really cares about her students. I have never been a good writer but found this class a lot easier than previous writing courses (CO150). She gives great feedback and wants her students to succeed. It is possible to get an A, time and effort is all!!
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Caring

comment: Frustrating professor. I have never struggled so hard to get an A. Easy to get a B or C in her class but the work is tedious and annoying. There are constant pointless quizzes and readings that rarely relate to the class and are just a time consumer. She is very picky about how she grades. Easy to get along with but this was my most annoying class.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Tough grader

comment: Dr. Morse does grade extremely hard, however, the workload lightens up towards the end of the semester. She also starts to lighten up as the semester goes on. Make sure to do the LO's and Hw and you will be fine.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--SO MANY PAPERS

comment: Worst teacher I have ever had at CSU. She will give you an extremely low grade because of things that are completely insignificant. Avoid her at all costs.

Take every rating on here lightly. Yes, Dr. Morse is a strict professor. Yes, this class is difficult. Except, this class is one that you need in your future business life. This professor cares if you care. Don't piss her off, and show effort. You're in college, the COB doesn't get easier.

Dr. Morse is the worst professor I have ever taken at CSU. She thinks she's funny when really her jokes are painful to listen to. Also class is a huge waste of time but you have to go because she takes attendance every day. She is an incredibly harsh grader and thinks she is a writing goddess. DO NOT TAKE HER CLASS

Jenny, at best, is mediocre. This was a very difficult class quite simply because of how much work is assigned between classes. You'd be better off trying to take an actual writing class to focus more on content rather than how pretty a message looks. Some of it is common sense. Group project toward end of semester worth good chunk of grade.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Gives good feedback--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: Avoid this teacher

Hard teacher, not flexible, this is a required course and otherwise no one would be there so we're miserable and she takes pleasure in that. But she is good at what she does, just treats you like kindergarteners.
Professor Halsey was extremely thorough in what she expected from us. She also gave several options to correct work for a better grade

Day was my favorite professor i've had at CSU so far! She makes her lectures so interesting and gives plenty of time to complete assignments. She is a tough grader, but so kind and really cares about each student.

This woman is seriously the best teacher I have had all four years of college. She is always saying things like "Isn't this just so fascinating" during her lectures, it's clear she has a passion for what she teaches. She is really good at responding to emails, having clear expectations/grading rubrics, and overall was just super kind.

Day is a very tough grader and since this class was online it was very hard to get in contact with her. Some of her assignment rubrics made no sense and when I looked at her syllabus her only method of contact was email or facetime. She is a tough grader, especially on the paper assignments which were assigned every week.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Get ready to read--So many papers

comment: Loved taking her class, she made it possible to earn a good grade while still making sure you got a lot out of the class. Weekly discussions, a research paper, and a project all of which she gives you a chance to turn in outlines/drafts for corrections. Exams are open book. She was easy to talk to and was easily accessible for questions.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Participation matters--Clear grading criteria

comment: Day makes this class so incredibly interesting! She uses great examples and allows everyone to pitch ideas. She also keeps it interesting with in class activities. The tests are easy and the projects are fun!

Day is absolutely wonderful! I love going to her class. I love her creative ideas. She is extremely involved in the HDFS department so she is able to answer almost any question you may have. She has tons of experience in this area, so listening to her lectures is entertaining and educational. I HIGHLY recommend taking her classes.
I've taken two classes with this professor and enjoyed both. He really makes sure you get exactly what you need - barely any busywork, good feedback, and a great sense of humor.

David was my favorite professor! He is straight forward about what content will be included on his exams. There are 3 exams and 3 papers throughout the semester, along with easy weekly quizzes online. He is a great guy and I would take if again if I had the chance!

Notes are not posted but the lecture is interesting and the exams only contain content from lectures, so if you go and take the notes you will do well. David is funny and knows what he's talking about. The information he provides is relevant and he presents it with high energy. I would recommend this class to anyone.

Attendance isn't taken, but it's best to show up to lectures because often in-class content comes up in exams and there are occasional in-class assignments worth points. Otherwise, the textbook and notes align with each other to make the simple five-minutes quizzes assigned no problem, the papers are easy if you follow the rubric.
ratingTags: Clear grading criteria--Hilarious--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: David is really knowledgeable about the subject and he makes his lectures interesting. He likes to joke around a lot, while also teaching you the material. Test are pretty easy because he lets you have notes and gives you a study guide. There are only a few papers and they are interesting because he gives you some freedom on the topics.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Participation matters--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS

comment: This is the best law class I have ever had as a non-legal studies major. David actually bothers to lay things out clearly, parse out the most important info for you, and lecture in a straightforward way that will help you understand and use the material. I **could not** have passed my future law classes without the experience from this class.

You can tell he's a lawyer from his lectures - they get heavy at times. But overall he's pretty funny and did a good job relating the material to students. JTC 100 is an easy class. He gives plenty of extra credit, and it's not a big deal if you miss a class here and there. The tests were fairly easy and there are 3 papers over the semester.

This teacher is a lecture heavy class. Need to show up to take notes, the lectures are super boring. If you can take a different teacher this class is super boring. These professors I will not take again. This class has online quiz the test are super easy and three papers through the semester. Their is also recitation three or four times a semeste.

You don't need to buy the book for Com Law, he posts the lectures on the slides before class so if you look up the court cases on Google you'll be fine. I recommend doing this because he does cold call and knit pick on you, but it's all for learning. Learned a lot in the class and he's a great professor!
Easy tests, funny

Sometimes I felt like he was trying too hard to get the class to like him, but overall he's not a bad teacher. Relatively easy to listen to and knows enough about media. He also tried to let us out a little early on Fridays which was nice. Definitely an approachable professor.

If you need to take  an Ethics or Law course definitely take it with him! He makes lectures very entertaining and although he gives alot of cases you can use your notes on the exams! He full explains everything and is not a hard grader. His motto is "Rather than taking off points in your exams , I try to give you as many points as I can"
This class is entirely based on quizzes and exams. Most of the questions are very specific to the content, which doesn't feel like I am actually learning the material.

Roaul is the only one who teaches this class, which blows. This is by no means an easy class or material as it involves everything learned from PH121. Expecting this, I was also expecting Roaul to attempt to make the material easier to understand, to teach us. He does not teach the material well at all and actually made it more confusing for me.

Dr. Reiser is a really awesome professor, he makes the subject enoyable to learn with his, as stated before, "dry" sense of humor. The material is difficult and requires a lot of memorizarion, but he is great about clarifying any questions that you may have. The test is optional but i suggest that you buy it and keep up wiht the readings.

Dr. Reiser is an awesome professor.  I thought his dry sense of humor was hilarious. He simplifies the material A LOT so that it can be accessible for people of different backgrounds.  The Class was overall really good, aside from being at night.

People say he has a monotone and not to get into his section but he was a really good teacher. I don't think people got his dry sense of humor but I did and really enjoyed his lectures. His tests are hard but if you memorize all the muscles you'll be fine. He also tells you when you have quizzes so you know to be there.

Dana is amazing. You do need to put in effort to get a good grade and get something out of the class. She is sometimes unclear with assignments, but always willing to answer questions and go above and beyond for students. She cares a lot about your success and understanding. She's very engaging. I feel that she is under appreciated.

Syllabus was unclear - discussions were also vague but when asked, she said the criteria as to what to post was in the syllabus.  If you're missing page length requirements or have too many, you'll lose points.  If you don't discuss what she wants in her posts, deducts points. Hit or miss with this teacher - not bad but not great.
He is one of the best professors I have had. I hate writing with a passion, and he was able to make it interesting and bearable. I would recommend his CO300 class over anyone else's.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Accessible outside class--Get ready to read

comment: Sean is honestly one of the best profs Ive had at CSU. He cares about everyone of his students and is there solely to help you in any way. He helped my friend look over her job application and cover letter, he responds to emails fast, and through this whole online school thing he has been great. He is so funny and genuinely nice. Take this class

Mr. Waters was so funny and smart. working with him was like a new world opening up in front of me. he gave me so much great feedback on my writing that the way I think now is forever changed. he is inclusive and kind. deep and real. for sure take this man's class and show him respect.
Sean is the best. Smart and funny. Take this class!

Sean Waters is hands down one of the best professors at CSU. This is not a regular freshman level composition class. Not only are his lectures hilarious and entertaining, Waters improved my writing more than any other professor I have had previously. His stories are inspirational.  He not only prepares you for writing classes, but life in general.

I usually hate required writing courses, but this class was a welcome relief.   Waters  is very laid back and listens to his students' needs. He's super helpful and his lectures are entertaining. Probably the best teacher I've ever had!  Take this course if you like unstructured discussions and would like to legitimately improve your writing.
Do not take a class with this guy. He changes his mind all the time when it comes to due dates and does not stick to the syllabus.
ratingTags: Participation matters--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--SO MANY PAPERS

comment: I loved the class, he was funny and a great instructor, it is a comp class so there is a lot of writing but he's there to help you. Just don't get behind.

Sean had very interesting and useful lectures. A plus to the class is you get 2 weeks of no class! He is a very good instructor and will teach you how to be a better writer. As long as you follow the rubric and take notes on what he expects for projects, you will get a good grade.

I really liked this class! Sean was definitely a hard grader, but he made me think about how to be a better writer! I really liked that he made class interesting, or it would have been a really hard class to go to. He also taught us how to write a proper resume and cover letter, which is way more useful in my opinion than writing technicalities.
Sean is funny and smart. He presents things simply but also helps you see the complexity. He gives clear and detailed feedback. He is great to work with one-on-one during office hours.

Great teacher. Expect homework every single night. This professor is great for actually improving your writing and reading skills and I would highly recommend him. However, I worked my ass off, went in constantly for help, yet still only came out with a B. Don't expect to receive an A from this professor. Only about 5% of his class will.

don't get me wrong, he's a nice funny guy but hell take one look at something you worked on for hours and tell you its a solid B with no explanations.  If you want to meet with him, he wont be at his office hours.  He'll go through your paper and make numerous changes, then criticize his changes when he later grades it.  His course is frustrating.

Sean was probably my favorite professor this semester. He loves to put scenarios into real world situations, which I respect a lot. If you think you can write a paper the day before it's due and get an A though, don't get your hopes up. Sean loves to have people stop in for help- he will help a ton! He's also super hilarious and keeps class light.

Kinda hated my life while taking this class. I used to love writing, but he is looking for a specific style (his style) or you won't get higher than a C. Lots of work compared to other sections of CO-150. Interesting guy and content but get ready to put in multiple hours per class hour.

Humor is a big role in his lessons.  He likes to keep the class light while still getting things done.  He's never in office hours.  If he goes over your paper, most likely he'll criticize the things he's asked you to change.  If you spend 100 hours on something and you're proud of it, don't worry he'll give you a C.

Hard class! He gives out very little A's& is a pretty tough grader. Last assignment he only gave out 9 A's out of all CO150 classes he taught. Do not take this class if you are willing to put in A LOT of effort or just naturally an extremely good writer. If you're writing isn't the best, like mine, you will struggle even if you do all the work.
He is a really great teacher but his composition class was not easy.  I had to do a lot of reading and writing.  I really liked his class and learned a lot about writing.  Good teacher.

Sean must be one of the most interesting teachers i have ever had. He is smart, funny and know how to translate his material a class of teenagers. I highly suggest you take Sean's class. Its well worth it.

Jason LISTENS to everyone's opinions, and values ALL of his students. Classes get into deep and interesting discussions, because it's Sociology, and he takes time to take on challenging topics. Lectures are entertaining and informative, participation heavy, but not required, food drive for extra credit connects to real life! AWESOME!

Easy class with pathetic agenda pushing. Creates own definitions and uses outdated statistics with often wrong information. Instantly will shuts down any contrary arguments and label them "know it all students." Majority of class is wasted listening to off topic personal nonsense. Obvious overreliance on TA's as well.
Jason was a very caring and wonderful individual. His lectures are easy to follow and he posts them on Canvas, making it easy to access if you cant make it to class!

Downing is a super chill dude. He is dorky and makes lectures fun. There is about 4 exams and some solution papers and a few discussions. Exams are timed but open book, as long as you read the chapter and listen to lectures you will be good. If you need a easy diversity and global awareness class this is it.

This is an easy class to pass, but don't expect to learn much more than you already know about environmental issues. Do not follow the study guide, because it will not help you on the exams. Test questions are pulled straight from the book and are VERY specific with numbers, not concepts. Tests ALWAYS have questions on material not yet covered.

He has not responded to several of my emails now. And when he responded to one of them, he avoided the rest of the email which was a question about grading. I have emailed him twice since then and he has not responded to me. He told me he would have two of my assignments graded two weeks ago and hasn't. Also liberal-politics heavy. Clear agenda

I love Downing. He is so passionate about what he teaches and he is incredibly funny and entertaining. He was really easy to reach if you had any questions or concerns. He definitely shows his opinions in the course material, but he doesnt penalize you if you dont agree with his stance.

Took the online version of the class due to the pandemic but I wish I could have experienced his energy in real life such an amazing soul. Keeps it raw and real with you very hilarious and only teacher and class I actually attended the zoom meetings and watched the lectures without boredom. Best sociology teacher at CSU by far.  So many extra cred

JASON DOWNING IS THE BEST PROFESSOR YOU WILL EVER HAVE! He makes this class so entertaining, I would almost consider changing my major just to have another class with him. He outlines work very well and is specific on what you need to do/what he wants from you. He is generous with extra credit and is very understanding. He is THE BEST.

I was understand a very traumic situation and he didnt respond to the 13 emails I had sent him through out the semester and even with student case management he never took the time to be understanding, helpful, or accommodating for extreme circumstances. He was very unprofessional and sends emails stating he will ignore u to the general whole.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Downing is a passionate and careful professor. His lectures were the best part of my day and I would gladly take his class again.

I had downing in my first semester as a student. He is very funny and a great professor. Attendance is extra credit, but it helps a lot. Do not show up to class if you are not going to pay attention or use your phone, he will call you out. This class had a lot of papers, some of them long, but if you try your best you will end up with an A or B.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--EXTRA CREDIT--So many papers

comment: Jason is a wonderful human. The class has four short papers, one super long one, and four tests. He provides lots of extra credit (brought my grade up 10%). I loved his class and plan on taking his other one. He makes class interesting and fun. Attendance is not mandatory, but you should go because he is just that great!!

Downing is hands down my favorite professor I've ever had. He is hilarious, makes his lectures super entertaining, and there's barely any assignments. Only downside is the food matters paper. But he had SO much extra credit that it brought my grade from a 92 to 102! Cannot recommend this class enough

In hindsight, the textbook was probably necessary as the test questions were very specific. Not too hard but TONS of extra credit is offered through participation which brought a low B to an A. Super personal and truly cares. Highly recommend him for any SOC course

I love Jason he is such a great guy but SOC220 was more difficult than I expected it to be and it didn't need to be. He expects you to read every inch of the book and remeber a lot from his lectures even when information isnt on the PP slide. He gives lots of extra credit and you write 5 papers in total. Its a doable class but he makes you work.
ratingTags: Respected--Get ready to read--So many papers

comment: The directions for his writing assignments are usually unclear, and are written in such a way as to make his class seem more difficult/serious than it actually is. I emailed him about a contradiction in the directions for an assignment, but his reply only made things more confusing. Subsequently, I ended up writing much more than was necessary.
I really liked him. I took General Sociology online and he helped me thoroughly understand everything we were doing - he is also just a really cool person in general!!
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Inspirational--Graded by few things

comment: Assignments are easy but he is not-organized and affects his student's if they are not diligent in double checking due dates. Poor grader, takes too long to grade assignments. No lectures, doesn't really teach mostly wants you to read. Make sure you know APA citation format or else you will fail.

Jason is awesome!! Handles talking about controversial issues really well. His lectures were so fun and made 8ams more bearable. Participation comes from TopHat, which is all extra credit rather than required, so a good sentiment but it does cost money!! Assignments can be long but if you work ahead of time and organize yourself you're golden!

Jason is super cool! I had a lot of fun in his class and learned a lot. We discussed a lot of really important and controversial issues, but he makes sure you're in a safe, open-minded environment. He assigns few assignments and it's pretty easy to get an A. Just make sure you start the food matters paper asap!

This class requires you to put in an effort but is also super easy to pass if you put in the effort. Jason makes a huge 100 level class entertaining and engaging, which is not easy. He also truly cares to make his students aware of current social issues while making it clear that all political views are okay. He's really funny and is worth taking.

I have taken some classes with poor professors before, but none have ever given me the motivation to write a review about them before. 95% of lectures were Jason Downing's time to use his platform as a means of pushing his political agenda and virtue signal, while the other 5% was used to teach course material. Genuinely abysmal professor.

Such a cool guy. Loves what he teaches, talks about relevant issues. lecture heavy and textbook is key to exams. participation points are optional but not necessary. Everything is very clear. A lot of exams, but they are spaced out well. Best professor I've ever had

I LOVE JASON. I want to minor in soc now because of him. He is awesome!! Easy class you learn so much from him. He offers a lot of extra credit. 4 tests but no cumulative final. Final is during dead week! Watch about 5 movies. Hes great definitely recommend. Im taking his Soc220 class now too

Other than the food matter's paper, Jason's class has been my favorite this semester. He is super funny and make sure to get TopHat, it's so funny. His class is super interesting! His tests have some really straightforward answers and some that are more unclear. I was in a different SOC100 class and had to drop it and I'm so glad!

Jason is hands down the best professor I've ever had. He really cares about his students and makes sure everyone feels welcomed and respected. Attendance is optional, however showing up will improve your grade, he's very reasonable and makes sure it's possible for everyone to get an A if they try. His lectures are very interesting and engaging.

Jason is a great professor! I took this class online and it has been one of the best! If you read the textbook and do your assignments, the exam is straight forward. He has a clear way of grading and is not a tough one at all. He is very understandable and gives quick feedback. Definitely recommend.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Clear grading criteria--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: Jason was awesome! Lectures were entertaining and he clearly cares about the material. Reading the textbook is important and pay special attention to vocab. While participation is not required you can get extra credit from TopHat and you should watch the films he shows as he'll test on them. The final paper is very important but relatively easy.

There's good and there's bad. The good is the workload isn't bad, extra credit for participation and a food drive, and he's a chill guy sometimes. But, his lack of clear grading criteria drove me nuts. No rubrics, assignments are very vague, and minimal feedback. Overall, do the EC and work a little, you'll get an A or B. Just might be frustrating.
hes absolutely hilarious. I took his soc 220 class and it was easy and entertaining. attendance is based from an app so you can get participation from home whenever you skip.
Love Him and I love his class! I would totally take his class again in a heart beat! His lectures are fun and his assignments doable.

Class felt more like listening to his political opinions than actually learning about sociology. I understand that we can't expect people to be totally nonpartisan but come on... Also seemed like you would get a 100% on everything just for trying. Would not recommend if you actually want to learn something that you couldn't hear from MSNBC.

SOC100 with Jason was an easy A, but more than that he really is a great professor. He connects all of his lectures to applicable situations to really put them in perspective. Going to class and participating in the end of the semester food drive will boost your grade almost a whole letter grade, so I definitely recommend both.

Jason is WOKE. Seriously my favorite professor ever. His lectures are interesting, he has great taste in music, and his class is pretty easy. His exams are really easy as long as you read the textbook. Dude really has me considering adding a sociology minor. if you don't have him as a professor you're missing out!

Jason is the dude. Such a kind and down to earth professor. He is so funny and always makes a 9 am class enjoyable. Plays good music before class starts. Study for the test and read the textbook and you will do good. Gives lots of extra credit. and again he is just awesome. TAKE HIS CLASS. Best soc 100 teacher out there

Jason is funny and very laid back but he has way to many papers then necessary and his TAs are oddly strict with them. He is an easy grader with his exams (curves them) and gives tons of extra credit. If you want to do well, make sure you read the text books because his lectures are not helpful or useful.

Jason was probably my favorite teacher this semester. He is really funny and makes the class interesting. There are content assignments for assignments that are single-spaced, 11 pt font. You do use the textbook. The tests are hard, but just study and should be fine. Attendance is mandatory for clicker points. Overall satisfied with this class.

This is the most laid back humanities classes I have ever taken. Lectures are interesting and relevant to everyone and the tests are so easy all you need is common sense to get an A. Lots of extra credit at the end which involves a food donation, so if you take this class you will also be helping your community.

I absolutely loved this professor. Jason is a very interesting guy and you can tell he has a great personality. The lecture material was not difficult to comprehend but I would highly advise attending his lectures and read the chapters. He will work with you on grades and will take most late work You will not regret taking this class.
Great professor, funny and really cares about his material. Gives tons of extra credit opportunity and minimal assignments. Tests can be hard, but as long as you use the book you'll be fine.

Jason is my favorite professor Ive had. He is very passionate about what he teaches and is a very effective teacher. He is a great guy overall that will make you care about what youre learning. He also understands that exams arent the end all be all when it comes to education. Great professor!
hilarious and just a good guy all around

Took SOC 100 with Jason, we were assigned a 10 page, single spaced, 11 pt font paper on food ingredients for a 100 level class. Uses "tophat" participation app, figured out that it works from anywhere and you can skip class and still get participation. Tests are hard and his powerpoints are confusing. He thinks he's funny but not worth it, trust me
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--SO MANY PAPERS

comment: Jason is by far one of my favorite professors at CSU. This class was great because it wasn't all about the information, made comparisons to everyday life. Very interesting, I learned a lot from him. Class is always a good time. The essay assignments are easy as long as you show effort. Make sure to attend class to collect valuable tophat points.

Professor Downing was poor at communication, taking weeks to respond or not responding at all and rarely posted announcements or updates.  He cares about his students and wants them to succeed, but I found the course to be very unorganized. There was no syllabus and assignments were sometimes a surprise. The exam instructions were also deceiving.

This beautiful man has made me rethink every move I take toward our environment. The way he looks and teaches makes me think that he could possible be Jesus. He he created his own religion, I would convert, no questions asked. He cares more about you, than you care about you. As hard as that is to believe, if you take his class, you will understand
great professor. he knows what he's talking about and has a great personality. if you go to class it is pretty easy. posts slides so you're able to miss a class.

Do not take his online class. Not once have I had trouble with online courses until this guy. So unclear about EXACTLY what he wants from you as a student. Also, quite rude and patronizing in feedback. I should have reviewed this site before signing up for his class.

This guy, even though i was in a lecture hall with about 200 other students, he made me feel like i was important to him. Like my presence and my effort mattered to him a lot. Such a great guy. Really good at keeping everything interesting and keeping us all involved. I learned a lot from him and wish i could take his class again. LOVE YOU JASON

Jason was such a great professor.  I had the opportunity to have Jason for an online class, Comparative Majority - Minority Relations during the Summer session.  He was always encouraging, helpful and organized on the online platform.  I really learned quite a bit from the questions and assignments that he had us complete.

Professor Downing was great! I recommend getting the book and taking note for the lectures. He gives GREAT extra credit if you attend class and donate to a canned food drive. Would take one of his classes again!

Jason is overall a good guy. Very liberal, just be tolerant if that's not the way you lean, what do you expect its sociology. I liked him a lot, at times he goofed off in class to keep it interesting, which was good. He cares a lot about the students. Minimal homework with one 10-15 page paper at the end which is not as bad as it sounds.

Jason Downing, though he be a total hippie, is an amazing and enjoyable professor. He is passionate about sociology and his lectures are hilarious. His class is incredibly easy. Show up to class for the TopHat (like iclicker) points and do the reading for the content assignments and you will get an A.

I loved Jason's class. He is hilarious and a total hippie but one of the best teachers I have ever had. I learned so much. He is accepting of everyone's points-of-views and loves when you talk in class. Top hat points really add up so don't miss those! He is passionate about teaching sociology but more passionate about us becoming good people.

Great guy, very funny & always there if you have any questions or concerns. While it's definitely more on the mandatory side to go to class, he keeps his class interesting. I laughed a lot & really enjoyed the class & participation of other students. Four tests (the final was week before finals weeks), Tophat points, and a page essay almost weekly.
GO TO CLASS. It affects your grade. He is pretty funny though and i enjoy the class. He asks for a lot of class participation but all you have to do is click a multiple choice answer online

He posts the power-points online after each chapter lecture. However, if you do not go to class, you miss a lot of essential information that he talks about. The exams are pretty rough unless you take time to study and really understand the content. Overall, good class and good professor.

Pretty easy class, some lectures are fun but a lot of the content we had to learn on out own. Tests tend to have content that we have no learned about. He will NOT round grades (had an 89.7 and he didn't round up)
he's a great teacher, you can tell he genuinely cares about teaching us about the world and not just the required material. had this class at 9:30 in the morning and didn't even mind going

DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS! Worst professor I have had at CSU.  He provides zero objective feedback. The citation requirements change with every assignment.  He makes online learning difficult, do not take this class.  His grading criteria is subjective and constantly changes.  Do yourself a favor, chose a different professor.

Do NOT take this class online.  He does not participate AT ALL.  No teaching from him...none.  No organization.  Confusing assignment structure.  He doesn't communicate.  Worst online class experience I've had.
Great teacher! Went from an F to an A- in 3 days!
Great teacher, very enthusiastic about teaching the Global Environmental Issues class I had. Easy going and understanding.
Do not take his class online.

Jason is so enthusiastic about the material in the class that it will make you look forward to going. His tests are written by his TA's so they are kind of a hit or miss but if you study and show up to class you should be fine. If present for 90% of clicker questions you get 5% added to your grade and so forth.. Overall I suggest taking his class!
He was generally a good professor, but he is very opinionated. He is not helpful via email when students ask him for help.
Only use book to study or read ahead. No homework or reading assignments. 4 exams and 1 five page easy paper.
He is an excellent teacher who is very enthusiastic about subject matter. He is very encouraging. I can tell he enjoys teaching it. Jason Downing is very caring toward his students.
